### Nexus API - manual test flow
### Requires the "REST Client" VS Code extension (humao.rest-client).
### Run requests top to bottom with the "Send Request" link that appears
### above each one. Variables auto-chain between requests.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api

### 0. Health check (no auth)
GET http://localhost:4000/health

### 1. Admin login (use the credentials printed by `npm run prisma:seed`)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@nexus.local",
  "password": "ChangeMe123!",
  "actorType": "ADMIN"
}

###
@adminToken = {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 2. View the category tree (public - powers the enquiry wizard)
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories

### 3. View active services (public)
# @name listServices
GET {{baseUrl}}/services

###
@serviceId1 = {{listServices.response.body.data[0].id}}
@serviceId2 = {{listServices.response.body.data[1].id}}

### 4. Submit a multi-service public enquiry (no auth - this is the wizard submission)
# @name createLead
POST {{baseUrl}}/leads
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contactName": "John Doe",
  "phone": "9999999999",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "companyName": "Doe Enterprises",
  "services": [
    { "serviceId": "{{serviceId1}}", "questionnaireAnswers": { "notes": "Need a full interior redo" } },
    { "serviceId": "{{serviceId2}}", "questionnaireAnswers": { "notes": "Rooftop solar, 5kW" } }
  ]
}

###
@leadId = {{createLead.response.body.data.lead.id}}

### 5. Admin views the lead (should show 2 independent Lead Services)
GET {{baseUrl}}/leads/{{leadId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 6. Progress a Lead Service through the workflow (repeat with different toStatus values)
# First get a leadServiceId from step 5's response, then:
@leadServiceId = REPLACE_WITH_LEAD_SERVICE_ID_FROM_STEP_5

PATCH {{baseUrl}}/leads/{{leadServiceId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toStatus": "QUALIFIED"
}

### 7. Create a Quotation for the Lead
# @name createQuotation
POST {{baseUrl}}/quotations
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "leadId": "{{leadId}}",
  "discount": 0,
  "transportation": 500,
  "installation": 1000,
  "items": [
    { "serviceId": "{{serviceId1}}", "description": "Interior Design - Full Package", "quantity": 1, "unitPrice": 150000, "taxRate": 18 },
    { "serviceId": "{{serviceId2}}", "description": "Solar 5kW Installation", "quantity": 1, "unitPrice": 250000, "taxRate": 12 }
  ]
}

###
@quotationId = {{createQuotation.response.body.data.quotation.id}}
@quotationVersionId = {{createQuotation.response.body.data.version.id}}

### 8. Approve the Quotation (Admin records how the client confirmed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/quotations/versions/{{quotationVersionId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "approvalMethod": "PHONE"
}

### 9. Convert the Lead to a Client (generates login + emails credentials)
# @name convertClient
POST {{baseUrl}}/clients/convert/{{leadId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
@clientId = {{convertClient.response.body.data.id}}

### 10. Create a Project from the converted Lead
# @name createProject
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "leadId": "{{leadId}}",
  "clientId": "{{clientId}}",
  "quotationVersionId": "{{quotationVersionId}}"
}

###
@projectId = {{createProject.response.body.data.id}}

### 11. View the Project - check the derived aggregateStatus field
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 12. Issue an Invoice against the Project (freeform - GST per line item)
POST {{baseUrl}}/invoices
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "projectId": "{{projectId}}",
  "clientId": "{{clientId}}",
  "label": "Advance Payment",
  "items": [
    { "description": "Advance - 40%", "quantity": 1, "unitPrice": 160000, "hsnSacCode": "9954", "taxRate": 18 }
  ]
}

### 13. Check the Project's financial summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/invoices/project/{{projectId}}/financial-summary
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 14. Global search (try a phone number, lead number, or service name)
GET {{baseUrl}}/search?q=9999999999
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 15. Admin dashboard summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/dashboard/admin/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### =========================================================================
### EDGE CASE / "BREAK IT ON PURPOSE" CHECKS
### These are NOT covered by the golden path above. Run after step 15.
### Each one should FAIL with the stated error - if it succeeds instead,
### that module has a real bug.
### =========================================================================

### E1. Illegal status transition - should reject with 400
### (Try jumping straight to COMPLETED from a fresh Lead Service status of NEW)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/leads/{{leadServiceId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toStatus": "COMPLETED"
}

### E2. Multi-service enquiry atomicity - one bad serviceId should roll back the WHOLE lead
### Expect: 400 error, and NO new Lead created (check via GET /leads afterward - count unchanged)
POST {{baseUrl}}/leads
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contactName": "Atomicity Test",
  "phone": "8888888888",
  "services": [
    { "serviceId": "{{serviceId1}}" },
    { "serviceId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000" }
  ]
}

### E3. Converting an already-converted Lead - should reject with 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/clients/convert/{{leadId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### E4. Completing a Project while services are NOT all COMPLETED - should reject with 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### E5. Cancelling an invoice - number must be PRESERVED, not deleted or reused
# Replace {{invoiceId}} with the id from step 12's response
@invoiceId = REPLACE_WITH_INVOICE_ID_FROM_STEP_12

PATCH {{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Testing cancellation - invoice number should survive this"
}

### E5b. Fetch the same invoice - confirm status=CANCELLED, invoiceNumber unchanged, record still exists
GET {{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### E6. Overpayment - should reject if payment would exceed outstanding balance
POST {{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}/payments
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 99999999,
  "method": "Bank Transfer"
}

### E7. Quotation revision - old version must remain readable after revising
POST {{baseUrl}}/quotations/{{quotationId}}/revise
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transportation": 500,
  "installation": 1000,
  "items": [
    { "serviceId": "{{serviceId1}}", "description": "Interior Design - REVISED scope", "quantity": 1, "unitPrice": 175000, "taxRate": 18 }
  ]
}

### E7b. Fetch the quotation - confirm BOTH version 1 and version 2 appear in the response
GET {{baseUrl}}/quotations/{{quotationId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### E8. Unauthenticated request to an Admin route - should reject with 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/leads

### E9. Client trying to read another Client's conversation - should reject with 403
### (Requires two client logins to test properly - see checklist doc for setup)

### E10. Public route should NOT leak inactive/disabled services
### First disable a service as Admin, then confirm it disappears from the public list:
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/services/{{serviceId2}}/disable
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
GET {{baseUrl}}/services
